<plot>Howard Reilly recounts fond yet bittersweet memories of his late love Ethel in their Long Island home. He decides to embark on a trip to the park in which they first met and fell in love. Accompanied by a young man the two make a pilgrimage to a nearby park a place they have traveled to many day past "......the place where the water dances on her face....she call it IN THE GLIMMER".</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?263091</url></doc>
